.Dd February 23, 2026
.Dt MINIWEB 1
.Os OpenBSD
.Sh NAME
.Nm miniweb
.Nd OpenBSD-native C99 web server on enterprise refactor track
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl hv
.Op Fl b Ar address
.Op Fl c Ar connections
.Op Fl f Ar file
.Op Fl p Ar port
.Op Fl t Ar threads
.Op Fl l Ar file
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a lightweight HTTP server written in C99 for OpenBSD.
It provides a web dashboard and JSON APIs for metrics, networking,
manual page browsing, and package management.
.Pp
The current runtime uses a single
.Xr kqueue 2
dispatcher thread and a worker pool.
Expensive telemetry is sampled through feature-local samplers,
and cached payloads are served to reduce handler latency.
.Pp
.Nm
is now under an enterprise refactor program that preserves all existing
features while introducing modular architecture, centralized heartbeat
scheduling, and a reusable sqlite3 storage interface.
.Pp
The implementation must remain strictly C99 and follow OpenBSD KNF.
.Sh OPTIONS
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl b Ar address
Bind to an IPv4 address.
Default is
.Cm 127.0.0.1 .
.It Fl c Ar connections
Maximum concurrent connections.
Default is
.Cm 1280 .
.It Fl f Ar file
Load configuration from
.Ar file .
.It Fl h
Print usage and exit.
.It Fl l Ar file
Append logs to
.Ar file
instead of stderr.
.It Fl p Ar port
Listen TCP port.
Default is
.Cm 9001 .
.It Fl t Ar threads
Worker thread count.
Default is
.Cm 4 .
Current compile-time maximum is
.Cm 32 .
.It Fl v
Enable verbose logging.
.El
