.Sh ENTERPRISE REFACTOR PROGRAM
The approved engineering direction is documented in
.Pa docs/ENTERPRISE_REFACTOR_PLAN.md .
.Pp
The program introduces a capability-based layout:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Pa core/
for lifecycle, heartbeat, config, logging.
.It
.Pa net/
for server accept loop, work queues, and connection ownership.
.It
.Pa http/
for parser, response writer, static files, MIME policy.
.It
.Pa router/
for route registry and module attach contracts.
.It
.Pa modules/
for feature bundles (metrics, networking, man, packages, views).
.It
.Pa platform/openbsd/
for native collectors (sysctl/getifaddrs/getmntinfo wrappers).
.It
.Pa render/
for template cache and rendering logic.
.It
.Pa storage/
for sqlite3 database and schema helpers.
.El
.Pp
Planned route/module extensibility uses an attach API so views and JSON
endpoints can be enabled or disabled without central route rewrites.
.Pp
Planned performance model replaces multiple feature-owned samplers with
one global 1-second heartbeat scheduler that dispatches periodic tasks.
.Sh IMPLEMENTATION STATUS
.Bl -tag -width "Storage layer"
.It Routing
Implemented with static table + dynamic prefixes.
Module-owned attach API is planned.
.It Sampling
Metrics and networking each maintain their own 1-second loops.
Unified heartbeat scheduler is planned.
.It Storage layer
Current caches are in-memory and filesystem based.
Reusable sqlite3 facade is planned.
.It File organization
Current tree contains large multi-responsibility files.
Capability-based modular tree is planned.
.El
.Sh DESIGN REQUIREMENTS
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
C99-only codebase.
.It
OpenBSD KNF style.
.It
Small per-function decomposition.
.It
Doxygen documentation for exported APIs.
.It
Compatibility-first refactor (feature parity required).
.El
